tldr: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app. I implemented a comprehensive sleep-themed design,
  including a new color palette, redesigned layout, and consistent styling
  across all sections. I also fixed a console error and refined the report
  section colors based on user feedback.
overview: "The user initiated a request to significantly enhance the aesthetics
  of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was visually
  lacking. I began by conducting a detailed analysis of the existing design,
  pinpointing areas such as a generic color palette, uninspired backgrounds, and
  basic form elements that needed improvement. The implementation proceeded in
  several stages: first, a new, calming sleep-themed color palette was
  introduced using OKLCH, along with custom gradients and shadows. The main form
  layout, progress bar, and intro section were redesigned with new visual
  elements like decorative blurs and feature cards. Core UI components such as
  checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards were also enhanced for a more
  polished appearance. Following this, consistent styling was applied across all
  questionnaire sections, replacing old gray boxes with themed card-like
  groupings, and updating alert components to align with the new theme. A React
  console error related to  values in input fields was identified and
  resolved by modifying the  component to handle these values gracefully.
  Finally, based on direct user feedback and a provided screenshot, the
  inconsistent card header colors in the report section were unified to match
  the overall sleep-themed gradient. The outcome is a visually cohesive,
  professional, and calming sleep questionnaire app with a consistent aesthetic
  throughout."
